And the test expects this behavior:
1. It has a document with `<title>   Hello\nthere   \n   now   \n`
2. It expects the result to be "Hello there now" (with normalised spaces, not just trimmed)

The current implementation just trims the text, but the expectation is to normalize whitespace (convert multiple spaces, tabs, newlines to single spaces, and trim). The `titleEl.text()` method already normalizes whitespace within the element, but then it's only trimmed.

